jQuery(document).ready(function ($) {
$('li#enrschedlink a').addClass('enractive');

$('#searchInput').on('input', function (e) {
if (e.which == 13) { return false; }

$(".enrpanel").show();
if ($("#searchInput").val()) {
$(".enrpanel:not([value*='" + $("#searchInput").val() + "' i])").hide();
}
});

if (window.location.hash) {
var htag = window.location.hash;
htag = htag.replace("#", "");
$('a[name="' + htag + '"]').next().next().show();
window.location.hash = htag;
}

$('a.enrtrigger').on('click', function () {
if ($(this).parent().parent().next().is(':hidden')) {
$('.enrpanel-body').slideUp();
$(this).parent().parent().next().slideDown();
}
else {
$(this).parent().parent().next().slideUp();
}
return false;
});
$('.enrpanel-body a[href*="#"]').on('click', function () {
htag = $(this).attr('href').split('#')[1];
if (htag)
$('a[name="' + htag + '"]').next().next().show();
});
$('#enrollware-reg img').css("max-width", "100%");
$('#enrollware-reg img').css("height", "auto");
});
</script>

float: left; margin-right: 5px;" loading="lazy"> <div style="font-weight: normal; font-size: 85%; color: gray; clear: both;"> <i>Instructor-led Classroom for Expired or New BLS</i> </div></a></span></div><div class='enrpanel-body'><div style="text-align: center; background-color: #3a5289; color: white; padding: 10px; font-weight: bold !important;">AHA BLS Provider &ndash; In-Person &ndash; Initial</div>
<!-- Image with Floated Text Wrapping -->
<p style="text-indent: 0px !important; margin: 0 !important; padding: 0 !important;"><img style="float: right !important; padding: 7px !important; margin: 0 0 10px 10px !important;" src="https://www.enrollware.com/sitefiles/coastalcprtraining/Class_Images/USER_SCOPED_TEMP_DATA_orca-image-951419333%5B1%5D.jpg" alt="BLS Initial Class" width="250" height="160" /></p>
<!-- Description -->
<p style="text-align: justify; text-indent: 0px !important; margin: 0 !important;">This American Heart Association (AHA) Basic Life Support (BLS) Provider course is designed for healthcare professionals who are taking BLS for the first time or whose certification has expired. It provides foundational skills needed to recognize life-threatening emergencies and respond with high-quality CPR and AED use.</p>
<p style="text-align: justify; text-indent: 0px !important; margin: 0 !important;">Course content is delivered through instructor-led training, hands-on practice, and scenario-based instruction covering adult, child, and infant CPR.</p>
<div style="clear: both;">&nbsp;</div>
<!-- Reference Material -->
<p style="text-align: justify; text-indent: 0px !important; margin: 0 !important;">We recommend reviewing the <strong><a style="color: #005184 !important; text-decoration: none !important;" href="https://www.enrollware.com/sitefiles/coastalcprtraining/CCC%20CLASS%20FORMS/2020BLSSummary%5B1%5D.pdf">BLS Quick Reference Guide</a></strong> before class.</p>
<!-- Course Details -->
<p style="text-indent: 0px !important; margin: 0 !important;"><strong>Course Highlights:</strong></p>
<ul style="text-indent: 0px !important; margin-left: 15px !important;">
<li>High-quality CPR for adults, children, and infants</li>
<li>Use of AED and relief of choking</li>
<li>Effective team dynamics and communication</li>
<li>BLS Chain of Survival and emergency response steps</li>
</ul>
<p style="text-indent: 0px !important; margin: 0 !important;"><strong>What to Expect:</strong></p>
<p style="text-indent: 0px !important; margin: 0 !important;">This class includes video instruction, instructor guidance, and supervised practice. Instructor-to-student ratio is 1:6 during skills sessions to meet AHA training standards.</p>
<p style="text-indent: 0px !important; margin: 0 !important;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="text-indent: 0px !important; margin: 0 !important;"><strong>Course Length:</strong></p>
<p style="text-indent: 0px !important; margin: 0 !important;">Approximately 3.5 to 4 hours</p>
<p style="text-indent: 0px !important; margin: 0 !important;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="text-indent: 0px !important; margin: 0 !important;"><strong>Certification:</strong></p>
<p style="text-indent: 0px !important; margin: 0 !important;">American Heart Association BLS Provider eCard (valid for 2 years), issued upon successful completion of the course requirements.</p>
<p style="text-indent: 0px !important; margin: 0 !important;">&nbsp;</p>

BLS Provider - In-person Renewal <img src="https://www.enrollware.com/sitefiles/coastalcprtraining/_AHA.png" style="width: 25px; float: left; margin-right: 5px;" loading="lazy"> <div style="font-weight: normal; font-size: 85%; color: gray; clear: both;"> <i>Instructor-led Classroom program for BLS Renewal</i> </div></a></span></div><div class='enrpanel-body'><!-- Header -->
<div style="text-align: center; background-color: #3a5289; color: white; padding: 10px; font-weight: bold !important;">AHA BLS Provider &ndash; In-Person &ndash; Renewal</div>
<!-- Image with Floated Text Wrapping -->
<p style="text-indent: 0px !important; margin: 0 !important; padding: 0 !important;"><img style="float: right !important; padding: 7px !important; margin: 0 0 10px 10px !important;" src="https://www.enrollware.com/sitefiles/coastalcprtraining/Class_Images/USER_SCOPED_TEMP_DATA_orca-image-951419333%5B1%5D.jpg" alt="BLS Renewal Class" width="250" height="160" /></p>
<!-- Course Description -->
<p style="text-align: justify; text-indent: 0px !important; margin: 0 !important;">This American Heart Association (AHA) Basic Life Support (BLS) Renewal course is designed for healthcare professionals with a current, valid AHA BLS Provider card who are seeking recertification. This course provides a focused review of core CPR and AED skills and allows participants to demonstrate continued competency in high-quality CPR.</p>
<!-- Prerequisite -->
<p style="text-align: justify; text-indent: 0px !important; margin: 0 !important;"><strong>Requirement:</strong> You must bring a current, valid AHA BLS Provider card to class. If your card is expired, please contact us prior to registration to verify eligibility.</p>
<!-- Ensure Container Doesn't Collapse -->
<div style="clear: both;">&nbsp;</div>
<!-- Course Style -->
<p style="text-align: justify; text-indent: 0px !important; margin: 0 !important;">This instructor-led, classroom-based course includes video instruction, skills demonstration, and scenario-based practice. Instructor-to-student ratio is maintained at 1:6 during hands-on sessions to meet AHA standards.</p>
<!-- Quick Reference -->
<p style="text-align: justify; text-indent: 0px !important; margin: 0 !important;">We recommend reviewing the <strong><a style="color: #005184 !important; text-decoration: none !important;" href="https://www.enrollware.com/sitefiles/coastalcprtraining/CCC%20CLASS%20FORMS/2020BLSSummary%5B1%5D.pdf">BLS Quick Reference Guide</a></strong> prior to class.</p>
<!-- Course Highlights -->
<p style="text-indent: 0px !important; margin: 0 !important;"><strong>Course Highlights:</strong></p>
<ul style="text-indent: 0px !important; margin-left: 15px !important;">
<li>High-quality CPR for adults, children, and infants</li>
<li>Use of AED and relief of choking</li>
<li>Effective team dynamics and communication</li>
<li>Opioid emergencies and maternity considerations</li>
<li>Hands-on practice with BVM, pocket mask, and two-rescuer CPR</li>
</ul>
<!-- Course Length -->
<p style="text-indent: 0px !important; margin: 0 !important;"><strong>Course Length:</strong></p>
<p style="text-indent: 0px !important; margin: 0 !important;">Approximately 3 hours (minimum per AHA PAM for BLS Renewal)</p>
<!-- Certification -->
<p style="text-indent: 0px !important; margin: 0 !important;"><strong>Certification:</strong></p>
<p style="text-indent: 0px !important; margin: 0 !important;">American Heart Association BLS Provider eCard (valid for 2 years), issued upon successful completion of all course components.</p>
<!-- CME Info - Retained -->
<div style="position: relative; width: 100%; margin: 20px 0;"><input id="toggleTable" style="position: absolute; opacity: 0; width: 0; height: 0;" type="checkbox" /> <label style="cursor: pointer; font-weight: bold; display: block; margin-bottom: 10px;" for="toggleTable"> (Click for information on potential CME credit.) </label>
<div id="tableContent" style="max-height: 0; overflow: hidden; transition: max-height 0.5s ease; background-color: #f9f9f9; padding: 0 10px;">
<p style="padding: 10px; text-align: justify; text-indent: 0px !important; margin: 0 !important;"><strong>Continuing Medical Education (CME) Credits:</strong><br /> The American Heart Association (AHA) authorizes the use of their courses for continuing education credits. The number of credit hours depends on the class and the accrediting agency.</p>
<p style="padding: 10px; text-align: justify; text-indent: 0px !important; margin: 0 !important;"><strong>Accrediting Agencies:</strong><br /> - American Medical Association (AMA): 1 credit = 1 hour.<br /> - American Nurses Credentialing Center (ANCC): 1 credit = 1 hour.<br /> - Commission on Accreditation for Pre-Hospital Continuing Education (CAPCE): 1 credit = 1 hour.</p>
<p style="padding: 10px; text-align: justify; text-indent: 0px !important; margin: 0 !important;"><strong>Credit Hours for AHA Courses:</strong><br /> - <strong>BLS Online:</strong> 0.25 credits per hour.<br /> - <strong>ACLS / PALS Online:</strong> 0.5 credits per hour.<br /> - <strong>In-Person Courses:</strong> Typically do not offer CME credits, except for specific regional requirements.</p>
<p style="padding: 10px; text-align: justify; text-indent: 0px !important; margin: 0 !important;">For more detailed information about how to claim your CME credits, refer to the official AHA guidelines or contact your licensing agency for specific requirements.</p>
</div>
</div>

BLS Provider - Online Class with in-Person Skill Session - Initial or Renewal <img src="https://www.enrollware.com/sitefiles/coastalcprtraining/_AHA.png" style="width: 25px; float: left; margin-right: 5px;" loading="lazy"> <div style="font-weight: normal; font-size: 85%; color: gray; clear: both;"> <i>Blended Learning HeartCode BLS</i> </div></a></span></div><div class='enrpanel-body'><!-- Header Section -->
<div style="text-align: center; background-color: #3a5289; color: white; padding: 10px; font-weight: bold;">AHA BLS Provider &ndash; Heartcode (Blended Learning)</div>
<!-- Image with Floating Fix -->
<p style="text-indent: 0px !important; margin: 0 !important; padding: 0 !important;"><img style="float: right !important; padding: 7px !important; margin: 0 0 10px 10px !important;" src="https://www.enrollware.com/sitefiles/coastalcprtraining/1828336.png" alt="Heartcode BLS Class" width="210" height="153" /></p>
<!-- Course Overview -->
<p style="text-align: justify; text-indent: 0px !important; margin: 0 !important;">The American Heart Association (AHA) Heartcode BLS course uses a blended learning format that includes an interactive online course followed by an in-person skills session. This format is ideal for healthcare professionals who need flexibility without compromising the required hands-on components of CPR training.</p>
<!-- Centered Image -->
<p style="text-align: center; text-indent: 0px !important; margin: 0 !important;"><img style="border: 1px solid #ccc; padding: 5px; box-shadow: 2px 2px 5px rgba(0,0,0,0.2);" src="https://www.enrollware.com/sitefiles/coastalcprtraining/Class_Images/HCBLS.png" alt="Heartcode BLS Online Course" width="350" height="200" /></p>
<!-- Course Description -->
<p style="text-align: justify; text-indent: 0px !important; margin: 0 !important;">Participants complete the online Heartcode BLS Provider course at their own pace and then attend a scheduled in-person skills session with an AHA Instructor. This allows for independent review followed by personalized feedback and evaluation of CPR skills.</p>
<!-- Course Highlights -->
<p style="text-indent: 0px !important; margin: 0 !important;"><strong>Course Highlights:</strong></p>
<ul style="text-indent: 0px !important; margin-left: 15px !important;">
<li>Complete the Heartcode BLS online course independently</li>
<li>Attend a 30&ndash;60 minute in-person skills session</li>
<li>Receive instructor feedback and hands-on practice</li>
<li>Demonstrate proficiency in high-quality CPR and AED use</li>
<li>Earn a two-year AHA BLS Provider eCard upon successful completion</li>
</ul>
<!-- Course Options -->
<p style="text-indent: 0px !important; margin: 0 !important;"><strong>Course Options:</strong></p>
<ul style="text-indent: 0px !important; margin-left: 15px !important;">
<li><strong>Heartcode BLS Access Code:</strong> Must be completed prior to the skills session. Course available at <a href="https://shopcpr.heart.org" target="_blank">shopcpr.heart.org</a>.</li>
<li><strong>Add-on Option:</strong> Heartsaver First Aid skills testing available during your appointment. Great for students or workplaces that require both CPR and First Aid certification.</li>
</ul>
<!-- Important Note -->
<p style="text-indent: 0px !important; margin: 0 !important;"><strong>Important:</strong><br /> Please email your AHA Heartcode BLS completion certificate to <a href="mailto:info@910cpr.com">info@910cpr.com</a> or bring a printed copy to your skills session. Completion is required for participation and eCard issuance.</p>
<!-- Non-Refundable Notice -->
<p style="padding-left: 30px; text-align: center; text-indent: 0px !important; margin: 0 !important;"><span style="font-size: 14pt;"><strong>** The AHA Heartcode course link is non-refundable once issued. **</strong></span></p>
<!-- Cancellation and Refund Policy -->
<p style="text-indent: 0px !important; margin: 0 !important;"><strong>Cancellation Policy:</strong><br /> You may reschedule your in-person session once with 48-hour notice. The AHA BLS Provider eCard is issued the same day as successful skills completion.</p>
<!-- CME Credit Information -->
<div style="position: relative; width: 100%; margin: 0 !important; text-indent: 0px !important;"><input id="toggleTable" style="position: absolute; opacity: 0; width: 0; height: 0;" type="checkbox" /> <label style="cursor: pointer; font-weight: bold; display: block; margin-bottom: 10px;" for="toggleTable"> (Click for information on potential CME credit.) </label>
<div id="tableContent" style="max-height: 0; overflow: hidden; transition: max-height 0.5s ease; background-color: #f9f9f9; padding: 0 10px;">
<p style="padding: 10px; text-align: justify; text-indent: 0px !important; margin: 0 !important;"><strong>Continuing Medical Education (CME) Credits:</strong><br /> The American Heart Association (AHA) authorizes the use of their courses for continuing education credits. The number of credit hours depends on the class and accrediting agency.</p>
<p style="padding: 10px; text-align: justify; text-indent: 0px !important; margin: 0 !important;"><strong>Accrediting Agencies:</strong><br /> - American Medical Association (AMA): 1 credit = 1 hour.<br /> - American Nurses Credentialing Center (ANCC): 1 credit = 1 hour.<br /> - CAPCE: 1 credit = 1 hour.</p>
<p style="padding: 10px; text-align: justify; text-indent: 0px !important; margin: 0 !important;"><strong>Credit Hours for AHA Courses:</strong><br /> - BLS Online: 0.25 credit per hour<br /> - ACLS / PALS Online: 0.5 credit per hour<br /> - In-person skills sessions may not be credit-eligible depending on your agency</p>
</div>

<div style="text-align: center; background-color: #a6192e; color: white; padding: 10px; font-weight: bold;">American Red Cross - Basic Life Support (BLS)</div>
<!-- Image with Floating Fix (Prevents Sidebar Issues) -->
<p style="text-indent: 0px; margin: 0; padding: 0;"><img style="float: right; padding: 7px; margin: 0 0 10px 10px;" src="https://www.enrollware.com/sitefiles/coastalcprtraining/_ARC.png" alt="ARC BLS Class" width="250" /></p>
<!-- Course Overview -->
<p style="text-align: justify; text-indent: 0px; margin: 0;">The <strong>American Red Cross Basic Life Support (BLS) Provider</strong> course is designed for <strong>healthcare professionals and first responders</strong> who need to develop or refresh their life-saving skills in a structured, hands-on environment.</p>
<p style="text-align: justify; text-indent: 0px; margin: 0;">This <strong>instructor-led course</strong> delivers <strong>high-performance CPR training</strong> with a strong focus on <strong>team-based response, real-world scenarios, and hands-on skill practice.</strong> It meets industry standards for emergency care training and ensures participants gain the confidence needed to respond quickly and effectively to cardiac and breathing emergencies.</p>
<!-- Ensure Container Doesn't Collapse -->
<div style="clear: both;">&nbsp;</div>
<!-- Course Topics -->
<p style="text-indent: 0px; margin: 0;"><strong>Course Topics Include:</strong></p>
<ul style="text-indent: 0px; margin-left: 15px;">
<li>High-quality CPR techniques for adults, children, and infants</li>
<li>Proper use of an Automated External Defibrillator (AED)</li>
<li>Airway management and ventilation techniques</li>
<li>Team-based resuscitation skills and communication strategies</li>
<li>Opioid overdose emergency response</li>
<li>Legal and ethical considerations in emergency care</li>
</ul>
<!-- Course Includes -->
<p style="text-indent: 0px; margin: 0;"><strong>Course Includes:</strong></p>
<ul style="text-indent: 0px; margin-left: 15px;">
<li>Instructor-led training with hands-on skills practice</li>
<li>Digital American Red Cross BLS Provider Certificate (Valid for 2 Years)</li>
<li>Engaging team-based learning scenarios</li>

BLS - Blended Learning Online - Initial or Renewal <img src="https://www.enrollware.com/sitefiles/coastalcprtraining/_ARC.png" style="width:25px;float:left;margin-right:5px;"><div style="font-weight: normal; font-size: 85%; color: gray;"><i>ARC Online Learning BLS with In-person Skills testing</i></div> </a></span></div><div class='enrpanel-body'><div style="text-align: center; background-color: #a41c1c; color: white; padding: 10px; font-weight: bold;">ARC - Basic Life Support (Blended Learning | Skills Session)</div>
<div style="font-weight: normal; font-size: 85%; color: gray;"><em>Complete your ARC BLS certification with online coursework and an in-person skills check.</em></div>
<p><img src="https://www.enrollware.com/sitefiles/coastalcprtraining/Scroll.png" alt="" height="20" /></p>
<div style="text-indent: 0px;">
<div><img src="https://www.enrollware.com/sitefiles/coastalcprtraining/_ARC.png" alt="ARC BLS" width="100" align="right" /></div>
<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>Train on your schedule with American Red Cross Blended Learning.</strong> This <strong>ARC Basic Life Support (BLS) Course</strong> combines <strong>self-paced online learning</strong> with a <strong>hands-on skills check</strong> led by an ARC-certified instructor. <strong>Once you complete the online course and test, bring your Certificate of Completion to your scheduled in-person session.</strong></p>
<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>&ldquo;Your certification, your way&mdash;engaging, efficient, and tailored to your needs.&rdquo;</strong> Blended learning lets you <strong>complete coursework at your own pace</strong> before testing your hands-on skills in a supportive, instructor-led setting.</p>
<h3> How It Works:</h3>
<ul>
<li><strong>Step 1:</strong> Receive a link to the ARC BLS online course and complete the coursework and test.</li>
<li><strong>Step 2:</strong> Schedule and attend an <strong>in-person ARC Skills Check</strong> with an instructor.</li>
<li><strong>Step 3:</strong> Upon passing, receive your <strong>2-year ARC BLS digital certificate</strong>, accessible anytime.</li>
</ul>
<h3> Who Should Take This Course?</h3>
<ul>
<li>Healthcare professionals needing ARC BLS certification</li>
<li>Medical and dental office staff, home healthcare workers</li>
<li>Anyone needing BLS training for work or school</li>
</ul>
<h3> Certification:</h3>
<p style="text-align: justify;">Upon successful completion, participants will receive a <strong>2-year Basic Life Support digital certificate</strong> with anytime, anywhere access to training records.</p>
<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>&ldquo;We respect your time and experience&mdash;CPR training that adapts to you.&rdquo;</strong> Our blended learning model ensures <strong>efficient training that fits your schedule</strong> while providing expert hands-on instruction when you need it.</p>

<div style="text-align: left; background-color: #b30000; color: white; padding: 10px; font-weight: bold;"> BLS Challenge &ndash; Assessment-Only Option for Experienced Providers</div>
<!-- Course Overview -->
<p style="text-align: justify; text-indent: 0px !important; margin: 0 !important;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="text-align: justify; text-indent: 0px !important; margin: 0 !important;">This is an <strong>assessment-only session</strong>&mdash;an American Red Cross BLS Challenge&mdash;designed for experienced providers who need to <strong>renew their certification</strong>. There is <strong>no instruction or remediation</strong> during this session.</p>
<p style="text-align: justify; text-indent: 0px !important; margin: 0 !important;">&nbsp;</p>
<!-- Important Notes -->
<p style="text-indent: 0px !important; margin: 0 !important;"><strong> IMPORTANT:</strong></p>
<ul style="text-indent: 0px !important; margin-left: 15px !important;">
<li>You must <span style="text-decoration: underline;">demonstrate all BLS skills</span> and <span style="text-decoration: underline;">pass a written test</span> to earn certification.</li>
<li>This is <strong>not a training course</strong>. You must already know the skills <strong>like the back of your hand</strong>.</li>
<li><strong>If you fail the Challenge</strong>, you will not be certified and must complete the full BLS course at a later date.</li>
</ul>
<!-- Preparation Note -->
<p style="text-align: justify; text-indent: 0px !important; margin: 0 !important;"> We <strong>strongly recommend</strong> that you purchase the ARC BLS Provider Manual (or use reliable online resources) to review and practice before attempting the Challenge. There are also <strong>non-endorsed YouTube videos</strong> that can help&mdash;search for "ARC BLS skills demonstration" for reference.</p>
<p style="text-align: justify; text-indent: 0px !important; margin: 0 !important;">&nbsp;</p>
<!-- Refund Policy -->
<p style="text-indent: 0px !important; margin: 0 !important;"><strong> No refunds for Challenge failures.</strong></p>
<p style="text-indent: 0px !important; margin: 0 !important;">&nbsp;</p>
<!-- Confidence Statement -->

Wilmington: 4018 Shipyard Blvd @ 910CPR's Office</span></a></li></ul></div></div><div class='enrpanel' value='HSI BLS and Adult First Aid | Blended Learning <img src="https://www.enrollware.com/sitefiles/coastalcprtraining/_HSI.png" style="width:25px !important; float:left !important; margin-right:5px !important; vertical-align: middle !important;"> <div style="font-weight: normal !important; font-size: 85% !important; color: gray !important; clear: both !important;"> <i>Online Coursework with In-Person Skills Testing</i> </div>'><a name='ct445670'></a><div class='enrpanel-heading'><span class='enrpanel-title'><a class='enrtrigger' href='#'>HSI BLS and Adult First Aid | Blended Learning <img src="https://www.enrollware.com/sitefiles/coastalcprtraining/_HSI.png" style="width:25px !important; float:left !important; margin-right:5px !important; vertical-align: middle !important;"> <div style="font-weight: normal !important; font-size: 85% !important; color: gray !important; clear: both !important;"> <i>Online Coursework with In-Person Skills Testing</i> </div></a></span></div><div class='enrpanel-body'><!-- Header Section -->
<div style="text-align: center; background-color: #3a5289; color: white; padding: 10px; font-weight: bold;">HSI BLS and Adult First Aid &ndash; Blended Learning</div>
<!-- Image with Floating Fix -->
<p style="text-indent: 0px !important; margin: 0 !important; padding: 0 !important;"><img style="float: right !important; padding: 7px !important; margin: 0 0 10px 10px !important;" src="https://www.enrollware.com/sitefiles/coastalcprtraining/Class_Images/HSI_BLS_FA_BL.jpg" alt="HSI Blended Class" width="210" /></p>
<!-- Course Overview -->
<p style="text-align: justify; text-indent: 0px !important; margin: 0 !important;">This HSI blended learning course combines <strong>Basic Life Support (BLS)</strong> and <strong>Adult First Aid/CPR/AED</strong> into a single certification. It's perfect for workplaces that need both credentials to meet insurance or licensing requirements. Participants complete an online course and then attend a brief in-person skills session with an authorized HSI instructor.</p>
<p style="text-align: justify; text-indent: 0px !important; margin: 0 !important;">&nbsp;</p>
<!-- Centered Image -->
<p style="text-align: center; text-indent: 0px !important; margin: 0 !important;"><img style="border: 1px solid #ccc; padding: 5px; box-shadow: 2px 2px 5px rgba(0,0,0,0.2);" src="https://otis.osmanager4.com/assets/images/otis.png" alt="HSI Blended Online Course" width="200" /></p>
<p style="text-align: center; text-indent: 0px !important; margin: 0 !important;">&nbsp;</p>
<!-- Course Description -->
<p style="text-align: justify; text-indent: 0px !important; margin: 0 !important;">Once registered, students receive a link to the online portion, which covers adult CPR, AED use, First Aid basics, and professional-level BLS topics such as team response, airway support, and high-performance compressions. After completing the online section, students attend a short in-person session to demonstrate hands-on skills and receive real-time feedback.<br /><br /></p>
<!-- Course Highlights -->
<p style="text-indent: 0px !important; margin: 0 !important;"><strong>Course Highlights:</strong></p>
<ul style="text-indent: 0px !important; margin-left: 15px !important;">
<li>One card covers both Adult First Aid and BLS</li>
<li>Ideal for professional offices, medical/dental staff, and facilities requiring dual compliance</li>
<li>Complete the online course at your own pace</li>
<li>Attend a 30&ndash;60 minute in-person skills session</li>
<li>Earn a two-year HSI certification upon successful completion</li>
</ul>
<!-- Real-World Relevance -->
<p style="text-align: justify; text-indent: 0px !important; margin: 10px 0 !important; background-color: #f3f7ff; padding: 10px; border-left: 4px solid #3a5289;"><em>This little-known 'combo' class was&nbsp;hiding in plain sight&mdash; but, it was exactly what a local ABA center needed and didn&rsquo;t know existed. They were facing a $120+ per person AHA combo (Heartcode BLS + Heartsaver First Aid + skills session) just to meet TRICARE and TRILLIUM requirements. We helped them uncover this streamlined HSI alternative &mdash; and now it&rsquo;s available for others in the same spot.</em></p>
<p style="text-indent: 0px !important; margin: 0 !important;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="text-indent: 0px !important; margin: 0 !important;"><strong>Course Options:</strong></p>
<ul style="text-indent: 0px !important; margin-left: 15px !important;">
<li><strong>HSI Blended Course Link:</strong> Provided after registration. Must be completed prior to your scheduled skills session.</li>
<li><strong>Group Option:</strong> Onsite training and flexible scheduling available for businesses or organizations with 5 or more participants.<br /><br /></li>
</ul>
<!-- Important Note -->

<div style="text-align: left; background-color: #006747; color: white; padding: 10px; font-weight: bold;"> HSI BLS Challenge &ndash; Assessment-Only Option for Experienced Providers</div>
<!-- Course Overview -->
<p style="text-align: justify; text-indent: 0px !important; margin: 0 !important;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="text-align: justify; text-indent: 0px !important; margin: 0 !important;">This is an <strong>assessment-only session</strong>&mdash;an <strong>HSI BLS Challenge</strong>&mdash;designed for experienced healthcare providers who need to <strong>renew their certification</strong> without instructor-led training. There is <strong>no instruction or remediation</strong> during this session.</p>
<p style="text-align: justify; text-indent: 0px !important; margin: 0 !important;">&nbsp;</p>
<!-- Important Notes -->
<p style="text-indent: 0px !important; margin: 0 !important;"><strong> IMPORTANT:</strong></p>
<ul style="text-indent: 0px !important; margin-left: 15px !important;">
<li>You must <span style="text-decoration: underline;">successfully demonstrate all required BLS skills</span> and <span style="text-decoration: underline;">pass a written exam</span> to receive certification.</li>
<li>This is <strong>not a teaching course</strong>. You must arrive confident and prepared to test out.</li>
<li><strong>If you do not pass</strong>, you will need to enroll in the full BLS course for certification.</li>
</ul>
<!-- Preparation Note -->
<p style="text-align: justify; text-indent: 0px !important; margin: 0 !important;"> We <strong>highly recommend</strong> reviewing the HSI BLS Provider Manual or using trusted online resources to refresh your skills beforehand. YouTube can also be helpful&mdash;search &ldquo;HSI BLS skills demo&rdquo; to get a sense of what&rsquo;s expected.</p>
<p style="text-align: justify; text-indent: 0px !important; margin: 0 !important;">&nbsp;</p>
<!-- Refund Policy -->
<p style="text-indent: 0px !important; margin: 0 !important;"><strong> No refunds for unsuccessful attempts.</strong></p>
<p style="text-indent: 0px !important; margin: 0 !important;">&nbsp;</p>

<table style="width: 263px; border-collapse: collapse; height: 291px;">
<tbody>
<tr>
<td style="padding: 7px; border: none; text-align: right;"><img style="display: block; border: none; margin: 0 auto;" src="https://www.enrollware.com/sitefiles/coastalcprtraining/Class_Images/AHAACLS.png" alt="ACLS Class" width="250" /></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
<p style="text-align: justify;">The Advanced Cardiac Life Support (ACLS) course is designed for healthcare professionals involved in the management of cardiopulmonary emergencies and resuscitation. This in-person, instructor-led training follows American Heart Association guidelines and emphasizes high-performance team dynamics and clinical decision-making in critical situations.</p>
<p style="text-align: justify;">This course is intended for personnel in emergency response, emergency medicine, intensive care, and critical care units. You may add an optional BLS renewal during registration if both certifications are needed.</p>
<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>Course Topics Include:</strong></p>
<ul style="text-align: justify;">
<li>Early recognition and management of respiratory and cardiac arrest</li>
<li>Airway management and related pharmacology</li>
<li>Post-cardiac arrest care and team communication</li>
<li>Identification and treatment of acute coronary syndromes and stroke</li>
</ul>
<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>Course Includes:</strong></p>
<ul style="text-align: justify;">
<li>Instructor-led classroom training with video-based and scenario-driven instruction</li>
<li>Hands-on station practice and skills testing</li>
<li>American Heart Association ACLS Provider eCard (valid for 2 years)</li>
</ul>

ACLS Provider &ndash; In-person &ndash; Renewal</div>
<p><img style="float: right; margin: 0 0 10px 10px;" src="https://www.enrollware.com/sitefiles/coastalcprtraining/Class_Images/AHAACLS.png" alt="ACLS Renewal Class" width="250" height="160" /></p>
<p style="text-align: justify;">This ACLS Renewal course is for experienced healthcare professionals who currently hold an active or recently expired ACLS certification. This instructor-led, scenario-based course helps reinforce and update your skills in managing cardiovascular emergencies.</p>
<p style="text-align: justify;">Course content includes advanced clinical interventions, team dynamics, airway management, rhythm recognition, pharmacology, and post-cardiac arrest care. This format is ideal for those working in emergency departments, ICUs, and other high-acuity settings.</p>
<h3>Course Topics Include:</h3>
<ul>
<li>ACLS algorithms and post-cardiac arrest care</li>
<li>Airway management and rhythm recognition</li>
<li>High-quality CPR and AED use</li>
<li>Team-based response and effective communication</li>
<li>Acute coronary syndromes and stroke management</li>
<li>Clinical decision-making in life-threatening scenarios</li>
</ul>
<h3>Course Includes:</h3>
<ul>
<li>Instructor-led classroom training and skills stations</li>
<li>Scenario practice and ACLS testing</li>
<li>American Heart Association ACLS Provider eCard (valid for 2 years)</li>
</ul>
<h3>Add BLS Certification:</h3>
<p style="text-align: justify;">You may add a BLS Provider Renewal to your registration to update both certifications in one session.</p>

ACLS Provider - Online or Skills Session <img src="https://www.enrollware.com/sitefiles/coastalcprtraining/_AHA.png" style="width:25px; float:left; margin-right:5px;"><div style="font-weight: normal; font-size: 85%; color: gray;"><i>Blended Learning HeartCode ACLS</i></div></a></span></div><div class='enrpanel-body'><div style="text-align: center; background-color: #c00000; color: white; padding: 10px; font-weight: bold;">AHA - ACLS Provider &ndash; HeartCode&reg; Skills Session</div>
<p><img src="https://www.enrollware.com/sitefiles/coastalcprtraining/Scroll.png" alt="" height="20" /></p>
<div>
<div><img src="https://www.enrollware.com/sitefiles/coastalcprtraining/steps.png" alt="ACLS Steps" width="322" /> <img style="margin-bottom: 10px;" src="https://www.enrollware.com/sitefiles/coastalcprtraining/Class_Images/ACLSHC.png" alt="ACLS Heartcode" width="250" /></div>
<p style="text-align: justify;">The <strong>ACLS HeartCode&reg; Skills Session</strong> is the hands-on component of the <strong>American Heart Association (AHA)</strong> ACLS certification. This session is for healthcare providers who have already completed the required <strong>online HeartCode&reg; ACLS course</strong>.</p>
<p style="text-align: justify;">During this <strong>in-person session led by an authorized AHA Instructor</strong>, you will demonstrate your ability to apply ACLS protocols, perform high-quality CPR, and manage simulated cardiovascular emergencies.</p>
<h3> <strong>How It Works:</strong></h3>
<ul>
<li>Step 1: Complete the <strong>HeartCode&reg; ACLS</strong> online course at your convenience</li>
<li>Step 2: Schedule and attend your in-person skills session</li>
<li>Step 3: Receive your <strong>AHA ACLS Provider eCard</strong> (valid for 2 years) upon successful completion</li>
</ul>
<h3> <strong>Course Highlights:</strong></h3>
<ul>
<li>Instructor-led ACLS practice and skills assessment</li>
<li>Scenario-based training in airway management and cardiac emergencies</li>
<li>Team dynamics, resuscitation leadership, and rhythm recognition</li>
</ul>
<h3> <strong>Course Options:</strong></h3>
<ul>
<li><strong>Need the online ACLS course?</strong> Select the <strong>HeartCode&reg; ACLS Course Link</strong> add-on during registration</li>
<li><strong>Want to renew BLS too?</strong> Add a BLS Provider Renewal for a combined certification experience</li>
<li><strong>Need both ACLS and PALS?</strong> Schedule skills sessions together after completing both online courses</li>
</ul>
<h3> <strong>Important Information:</strong></h3>
<p style="text-align: justify;">If you've already completed the online course, please bring your <strong>HeartCode&reg; ACLS completion certificate</strong> to your scheduled session or email it to <a href="mailto:info@910cpr.com">info@910cpr.com</a>.</p>
<p style="padding-left: 30px; text-align: center;"><img style="float: left; margin: 0px 10px;" src="https://d32pa7zymd21yl.cloudfront.net/pub/media/catalog/product/cache/1c36cdbe3649fe5626a79b79d64a74a3/1/5/15-1407_heartcode_acls_elearning_thumbnail.jpg" alt="Heartcode ACLS" width="198" /></p>
<p><strong> Please note: HeartCode&reg; ACLS course links are non-refundable.</strong></p>

float:left; margin-right:5px;"><div style="font-weight: normal; font-size: 85%; color: gray;"><i>Instructor-led Classroom for Expired or New PALS</i></div></a></span></div><div class='enrpanel-body'><div style="text-align: center; background-color: #c00000; color: white; padding: 10px; font-weight: bold;">AHA - PALS Provider &ndash; In-Person &ndash; Initial</div>
<p><img style="float: right; padding: 7px; margin: 0 0 10px 10px;" src="https://www.enrollware.com/sitefiles/coastalcprtraining/Class_Images/419E5E17-3F14-4EB5-AF25-995EB198E2D0%5B1%5D.jpeg" alt="PALS Provider Class" width="250" /></p>
<p style="text-align: justify;">The <strong>American Heart Association (AHA) Pediatric Advanced Life Support (PALS) Provider Course</strong> is designed for healthcare professionals who manage respiratory and cardiovascular emergencies in infants and children. This <strong>instructor-led, scenario-based class</strong> emphasizes the recognition and treatment of pediatric respiratory distress, shock, and cardiac arrest.</p>
<p style="text-align: justify;">This course is ideal for pediatricians, emergency and critical care staff, paramedics, and other providers involved in pediatric emergency response. Participants will apply AHA PALS algorithms, develop effective communication skills, and gain hands-on experience through realistic team scenarios.</p>
<h3> Course Topics Include:</h3>
<ul>
<li>Respiratory distress and failure recognition</li>
<li>Management of pediatric shock and cardiac arrest</li>
<li>Systematic pediatric assessment and PALS algorithms</li>
<li>Airway management techniques and related pharmacology</li>
<li>Effective team-based resuscitation and communication</li>
<li>High-quality CPR and AED use for infants and children</li>
</ul>
<h3> Required Textbook:</h3>
<p style="text-align: justify;">A current AHA PALS Provider Manual is required for this course. Choose between:</p>
<ul>
<li><strong>Printed textbook:</strong> Available at registration</li>
<li><strong>Digital eBook:</strong> Emailed upon registration</li>
</ul>
<h3> Add a BLS Renewal:</h3>
<p style="text-align: justify;">Need to renew BLS too? You may add the BLS Provider Renewal during registration. The skills check will be completed during your PALS session.</p>
<h3> Certification:</h3>
<p style="text-align: justify;">Upon successful completion, you will receive a <strong>2-year American Heart Association PALS Provider eCard</strong>, valid nationwide.</p>

Wilmington: 4018 Shipyard Blvd @ 910CPR's Office</span></a></li></ul></div></div><div class='enrpanel' value='AHA - PALS Provider - In Person - Renewal<img src="https://www.enrollware.com/sitefiles/coastalcprtraining/_AHA.png" style="width:25px; float:left; margin-right:5px;"><div style="font-weight: normal; font-size: 85%; color: gray;"><i>Instructor-led Classroom for PALS renewal</i></div>'><a name='ct251496'></a><div class='enrpanel-heading'><span class='enrpanel-title'><a class='enrtrigger' href='#'>AHA - PALS Provider - In Person - Renewal<img src="https://www.enrollware.com/sitefiles/coastalcprtraining/_AHA.png" style="width:25px; float:left; margin-right:5px;"><div style="font-weight: normal; font-size: 85%; color: gray;"><i>Instructor-led Classroom for PALS renewal</i></div></a></span></div><div class='enrpanel-body'><div style="text-align: center; background-color: #c00000; color: white; padding: 10px; font-weight: bold;">AHA - PALS Provider &ndash; In-Person &ndash; Renewal</div>
<p><img style="float: right; padding: 7px; margin: 0 0 10px 10px;" src="https://www.enrollware.com/sitefiles/coastalcprtraining/Class_Images/419E5E17-3F14-4EB5-AF25-995EB198E2D0%5B1%5D.jpeg" alt="PALS Renewal Class" width="250" /></p>
<p style="text-align: justify;">The <strong>American Heart Association (AHA) Pediatric Advanced Life Support (PALS) Provider Renewal Course</strong> is designed for healthcare professionals who currently hold a <strong>current or recently expired AHA PALS Provider card</strong>. This <strong>in-person, instructor-led course</strong> reinforces core pediatric emergency care skills through scenario-based instruction and hands-on practice.</p>
<p style="text-align: justify;">Participants will refine pediatric assessment strategies, strengthen clinical decision-making skills, and demonstrate team-based resuscitation techniques using the AHA PALS algorithm. This course is ideal for providers working in emergency departments, intensive care, or other high-acuity environments.</p>
<h3> Course Topics Include:</h3>
<ul>
<li>PALS algorithms and systematic pediatric assessment</li>
<li>Management of respiratory distress and failure</li>
<li>Recognition and treatment of pediatric shock and cardiac arrest</li>
<li>Airway management and pharmacology in pediatric emergencies</li>
<li>Team dynamics and effective communication during resuscitation</li>
<li>High-quality CPR and AED use for infants and children</li>
</ul>
<h3> Required Textbook:</h3>
<p style="text-align: justify;">The current AHA PALS Provider Manual is required for this course. Choose one at registration:</p>
<ul>
<li><strong>Printed manual:</strong> Available for shipping or pickup</li>
<li><strong>Digital eBook:</strong> Delivered via email for instant access</li>
</ul>
<h3> Add a BLS Renewal:</h3>
<p style="text-align: justify;">Need to renew both certifications? Add the BLS Provider Renewal option during registration and complete both on the same day.</p>
<h3> Certification:</h3>
<p style="text-align: justify;">Upon successful completion, you will receive a <strong>2-year American Heart Association PALS Provider eCard</strong>, issued the same day and valid nationwide.</p>

float:left; margin-right:5px;"><div style="font-weight: normal; font-size: 85%; color: gray;"><i>Blended Learning HeartCode ASLS</i></div></a></span></div><div class='enrpanel-body'><div style="text-align: center; background-color: #4799b5; color: white; padding: 10px; font-weight: bold;">Advanced Stroke Life Support&reg; (ASLS) Blended Learning Course</div>
<p><img style="float: right; padding: 7px;" src="https://www.enrollware.com/sitefiles/coastalcprtraining/Class_Images/ASLS_Cover_900x600_new_optimized%5B1%5D.jpg" alt="" width="360" height="240" /></p>
<p style="text-align: justify;"><br />The <strong>American Heart Association</strong>, in partnership with the <strong>University of Miami's Gordon Center</strong>, offers the <em>Advanced Stroke Life Support&reg; (ASLS) Blended Learning Course</em>. This course is designed for in-hospital and prehospital healthcare professionals to effectively identify, evaluate, and manage patients with stroke.</p>
<p><strong>Who Should Take This Course?</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Stroke Coordinators</li>
<li>Nursing Students and Nurses</li>
<li>Advanced Practice Registered Nurses</li>
<li>Paramedics and Emergency Medical Personnel</li>
<li>Physicians, Physician Assistants, Residents, Fellows, and Medical Students</li>
<li>Respiratory Therapists</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Course Options:</strong></p>
<ol>
<li><strong>Prehospital Provider Course:</strong> Focuses on stroke assessment, field management, and EMS-to-hospital communication.</li>
<li><strong>In-Hospital Provider Course:</strong> Covers acute stroke care, secondary prevention, and post-stroke planning.</li>
<li><strong>Combined Prehospital &amp; In-Hospital Course:</strong> Ideal for providers involved across the full continuum of stroke care or instructor candidates.</li>
</ol>
<h3 style="margin-top: 20px;"> Continuing Education Units (CEUs)</h3>
<p style="font-style: italic;">Below are the CEUs awarded for each ASLS course format:</p>
<p><strong> ASLS Online: Prehospital &amp; In-Hospital Provider</strong><br /> &bull; Physicians/AMA: 4.5<br /> &bull; Nurses/ANCC: 8.0<br /> &bull; RT/AARC: 6.25<br /> &bull; EMS/CAPCE: 6.75</p>
<p><strong> ASLS Hands-On: Prehospital &amp; In-Hospital Provider</strong><br /> &bull; EMS/CAPCE: 1.25</p>
<p><strong> ASLS Online: Prehospital Provider Only</strong><br /> &bull; EMS/CAPCE: 4.25</p>
<p><strong> ASLS Hands-On: Prehospital Provider</strong><br /> &bull; EMS/CAPCE: 1.00</p>
<p><strong> ASLS Online: In-Hospital Provider Only</strong><br /> &bull; Physicians/AMA: 4.25<br /> &bull; Nurses/ANCC: 5.25<br /> &bull; RT/AARC: 4.75</p>
<p><strong> ASLS Instructor Essentials Hands-On</strong><br /> &bull; EMS/CAPCE: 6.25</p>
<p style="font-size: 85%; color: gray; margin-top: 15px;"><em>ASLS&reg; is a registered trademark of the Gordon Center for Simulation and Innovation in Medical Education. <h2> HSI Pediatric First Aid | CPR AED (Blended)</h2>
<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>Be prepared. Stay calm. Take action.</strong> This nationally recognized <strong>HSI Pediatric First Aid | CPR AED &ndash; Blended (Guidelines 2020)</strong> course gives childcare professionals and families the skills to respond quickly to infant, child, and adult emergencies. The blended format combines convenient <strong>online learning</strong> with a brief, hands-on <strong>in-person skills session</strong> for real-world confidence and compliance.</p>
<ul>
<li> <strong>Part 1 &ndash; Online:</strong> Interactive modules you can complete on your schedule (mobile/desktop friendly)</li>
<li> <strong>Part 2 &ndash; Skills:</strong> Short, instructor-led practice and skills verification with manikins and AED trainer</li>
<li> <strong>2-year HSI certification</strong> upon successful completion</li>
<li> Ideal for <strong>licensed childcare</strong>, preschools, daycares, after-school programs, camps, babysitters, nannies, foster/adoptive parents, and youth-program staff</li>
</ul>
<h3> What You&rsquo;ll Learn</h3>
<ul>
<li> Medical emergencies: asthma, difficulty breathing, seizures, diabetic issues, severe allergic reaction (anaphylaxis)</li>
<li> Injury care: bleeding control, bandaging, burns, sprains/strains, fractures, head/neck/spine precautions</li>
<li>&zwj; Choking relief techniques for infants, children, and adults</li>
<li> High-quality CPR (infant/child/adult) and safe AED operation</li>
<li> Drowning and near-drowning response; post-rescue care</li>
<li> Bites, stings, and environmental exposures (heat/cold, poison)</li>
<li> Prevention spotlight: <strong>Shaken Baby Syndrome/Abusive Head Trauma</strong></li>
</ul>
<h3> Compliance at a Glance (NC DCDEE 10A NCAC 09 .1102)</h3>
<p style="margin: 6px 0; text-align: justify;">This course <strong>fulfills the CPR/First Aid certification piece</strong> and teaches several emergency topics child-care staff need. For <em>full</em> .1102 compliance, add the NC-approved trainings and your center&rsquo;s written policies listed below.</p>
<ul style="list-style: none; padding-left: 0; margin: 0;">
<li style="margin: 3px 0;"><span style="color: #2e7d32; font-weight: bold;"></span> Pediatric CPR &amp; First Aid (infant/child)</li>
<li style="margin: 3px 0;"><span style="color: #2e7d32; font-weight: bold;"></span> Prevention/response to food allergies &amp; anaphylaxis</li>
<li style="margin: 3px 0;"><span style="color: #2e7d32; font-weight: bold;"></span> Shaken Baby Syndrome / Abusive Head Trauma (prevention)</li>
<li style="margin: 3px 0;"><span style="color: #6b7280;"></span> Infectious-disease control &amp; <em>immunization program policies</em></li>
<li style="margin: 3px 0;"><span style="color: #6b7280;"></span> Medication administration &amp; <em>parental-consent standards</em></li>
<li style="margin: 3px 0;"><span style="color: #6b7280;"></span> Building/premises safety (electrical, water, traffic hazards)</li>
<li style="margin: 3px 0;"><span style="color: #6b7280;"></span> Emergency Preparedness &amp; Response (<em>written EPR plan + training</em>)</li>
<li style="margin: 3px 0;"><span style="color: #6b7280;"></span> Hazardous-materials handling &amp; biocontaminant disposal</li>
<li style="margin: 3px 0;"><span style="color: #6b7280;"></span> Child transportation precautions</li>
<li style="margin: 3px 0;"><span style="color: #6b7280;"></span> Recognizing/reporting child abuse, neglect, maltreatment</li>
<li style="margin: 3px 0;"><span style="color: #6b7280;"></span> SIDS prevention &amp; safe sleep (<em>ITS-SIDS</em>)</li>
</ul>
<p style="margin: 10px 0 0 0; font-size: 95%;"><strong>Finish the checklist:</strong> NC requires <em>ITS-SIDS Safe Sleep</em>, <em>Emergency Preparedness &amp; Response (EPR)</em>, <em>Medication Administration</em>, and <em>Recognizing/Reporting Child Maltreatment</em> trainings, plus your center&rsquo;s written policies for premises safety, hazards/biowaste, transportation, and immunizations.</p>
<h3> Service Area &amp; Options</h3>
<p style="text-align: justify;">Public classes and on-site group training are available across <strong>Southeastern North Carolina</strong> (Wilmington, Burgaw, Jacksonville, surrounding counties). Blended delivery keeps downtime low while ensuring hands-on practice and evaluation.</p>
<h3> Why 910CPR for HSI Pediatric Training?</h3>
<ul>
<li>Fast, flexible scheduling for skills sessions</li>
<li>Clear, practical instruction focused on real childcare scenarios</li>
<li>Digital certification and completion record for your files</li>
<li>Group/onsite pricing available for centers and schools</li>
</ul>

<p style="text-align: center !important; font-weight: bold !important;">The Dates/Times below are for a Hands-On Session (<em>Step 2</em>) for an AHA online course.</p>
<p style="text-align: center !important; font-weight: bold !important;">* If you need <em>Step 1</em>: Once you choose a date to test, you will be offered Class Type selections. <em>(e.g., First Aid CPR/AED, Pediatric First Aid CPR, etc.)</em></p>
<p style="text-align: center !important; font-weight: bold !important;">If you are seeking a <strong>Merchant Mariner First Aid Certification</strong>, add both <em>TOTAL</em> and the <em>AMERHA-216</em> options.</p>
<p style="text-align: center !important; font-weight: bold !important;">Bloodborne Pathogens can be added to any selection.</p>
<hr style="border-top: 1px solid #ccc !important; margin: 15px 0 !important;" />
<p style="text-indent: 0px !important; text-align: justify !important;">The Heartsaver Online courses are taught in a blended learning format. Students must complete the online portion, followed by the hands-on skills session conducted by an American Heart Association Training Center Instructor. Upon successful completion, students will receive a <strong>Heartsaver Course Completion Card</strong>, valid for 2 years.</p>
<p style="text-indent: 0px !important; text-align: justify !important;">The AHA&rsquo;s Heartsaver courses are designed for individuals with little or no medical training who require first aid and/or CPR training for job requirements, regulatory compliance (OSHA), or personal preparedness.</p>

<p>Learn to recognize and respond to the most common childhood emergencies with the <strong>American Heart Association&rsquo;s Heartsaver&reg; Pediatric First Aid CPR AED</strong> course &mdash; a must-have for anyone responsible for the safety of infants and children.</p>

<ul>

<li>&zwj; Asthma emergencies</li>
<li> Drowning response</li>
<li> Bites &amp; stings</li>
<li> Burns</li>
<li> CPR &amp; AED for <strong>children and infants</strong></li>
<li> Choking relief techniques</li>
<li>&zwj; (Optional) Adult CPR &amp; AED overview</li>
</ul>

<p style="text-indent: 0px !important; margin: 0 !important; padding: 0 !important;"><img style="float: right !important; padding: 7px !important; margin: 0 0 10px 10px !important;" src="https://www.enrollware.com/sitefiles/coastalcprtraining/1471S.png" alt="1471S" width="210" height="153" /></p>
<p style="text-align: justify; text-indent: 0px !important; margin: 0 !important;"><strong>&iquest;Prefiere aprender a su propio ritmo y a&uacute;n obtener pr&aacute;ctica en persona?</strong> El curso <strong>Heartsaver&reg; Primeros Auxilios con RCP y DEA en espa&ntilde;ol</strong> es una opci&oacute;n flexible ofrecida por la <strong>American Heart Association (AHA)</strong>. Primero, usted completar&aacute; la parte en l&iacute;nea en su propio tiempo desde cualquier dispositivo. Despu&eacute;s, asistir&aacute; a una breve <strong>sesi&oacute;n pr&aacute;ctica en persona</strong> para demostrar sus habilidades.</p>
<p style="text-align: justify; text-indent: 0px !important; margin: 0 !important;">Este curso est&aacute; dise&ntilde;ado para cualquier persona que necesite saber c&oacute;mo actuar en una emergencia m&eacute;dica com&uacute;n, incluyendo uso del DEA, maniobras de RCP, y atenci&oacute;n b&aacute;sica de primeros auxilios.</p>
<p style="text-indent: 0px !important; margin: 0 !important;"><strong>Pasos para completar el curso:</strong></p>
<ul style="text-indent: 0px !important; margin-left: 15px !important;">
<li>Recibir&aacute; por correo electr&oacute;nico un enlace para acceder al curso en l&iacute;nea (en espa&ntilde;ol).</li>
<li>Complete la parte en l&iacute;nea antes de la fecha de su clase pr&aacute;ctica.</li>
<li>Traiga su <strong>certificado de finalizaci&oacute;n</strong> impreso o env&iacute;elo por correo a <a href="mailto:info@910cpr.com">info@910cpr.com</a>.</li>
<li>Asista a la sesi&oacute;n pr&aacute;ctica en la fecha seleccionada para practicar y demostrar sus habilidades.</li>
</ul>
<p style="text-indent: 0px !important; margin: 0 !important;"><strong>Nota importante:</strong><br /> Su instructor no podr&aacute; emitir su certificaci&oacute;n sin el comprobante de finalizaci&oacute;n del curso en l&iacute;nea. Por favor, aseg&uacute;rese de haber completado la parte digital antes de asistir a la sesi&oacute;n pr&aacute;ctica.</p>
<p style="padding-left: 30px; text-align: center; text-indent: 0px !important; margin: 0 !important;"><span style="font-size: 14pt;"><strong>** El enlace al curso en l&iacute;nea no es reembolsable una vez enviado. **</strong></span></p>
<p style="text-indent: 0px !important; margin: 0 !important;"><strong>Pol&iacute;tica de cancelaci&oacute;n y reprogramaci&oacute;n:</strong><br /> Puede reprogramar su sesi&oacute;n pr&aacute;ctica una vez sin costo con al menos 48 horas de anticipaci&oacute;n. Su tarjeta digital de certificaci&oacute;n ser&aacute; emitida el mismo d&iacute;a de su sesi&oacute;n pr&aacute;ctica aprobada.</p>

<p style="padding: 10px; text-align: justify; text-indent: 0px !important; margin: 0 !important;"><strong>Want to learn at your own pace while still getting hands-on practice?</strong> The <strong>Heartsaver&reg; First Aid CPR AED course in Spanish</strong> is a flexible option from the <strong>American Heart Association (AHA)</strong>. First, you'll complete the online course on your own schedule from any device. Then, you'll attend a short <strong>in-person skills session</strong> to demonstrate what you've learned.</p>
<p style="padding: 10px; text-align: justify; text-indent: 0px !important; margin: 0 !important;">This course is designed for anyone who wants to know how to respond to common medical emergencies, including CPR, AED use, and basic first aid.</p>
<p style="padding: 10px; text-indent: 0px !important; margin: 0 !important;"><strong>Steps to complete the course:</strong></p>
<ul style="padding: 10px; text-indent: 0px !important; margin-left: 15px !important;">

<li>Attend the hands-on session to practice and demonstrate your skills.</li>
</ul>
<p style="padding: 10px; text-indent: 0px !important; margin: 0 !important;"><strong>Important note:</strong><br /> Your instructor cannot issue your certification without proof of course completion. Please ensure the online portion is done before your in-person session.</p>
<p style="padding: 10px; text-align: center; text-indent: 0px !important; margin: 0 !important;"><span style="font-size: 14pt;"><strong>** The course link is non-refundable once issued. **</strong></span></p>

Your digital certification card will be issued the same day you successfully complete your in-person session.</p>

In-Person Training</div>

</div>
<p style="text-align: justify;">The <strong>HSI Adult First Aid | CPR AED</strong> course is a <strong>nationally recognized, instructor-led program</strong> that teaches essential skills for responding to medical emergencies involving adults, children, and infants. Participants will learn how to provide high-quality CPR, use an AED, and offer effective first aid in real-world situations&mdash;from workplace incidents to home-based emergencies.</p>
<h3> <strong>Course Highlights:</strong></h3>
<ul>
<li><strong>Comprehensive Curriculum:</strong> Includes CPR, AED use, choking relief, bleeding control, burns, shock, and more.</li>
<li><strong>Evidence-Based Training:</strong> Follows the latest ILCOR resuscitation science and the 2020 AHA Guidelines for CPR and ECC.</li>
</ul>
<h3> <strong>Who Should Enroll?</strong></h3>
<p style="text-align: justify;">This course is ideal for <strong>non-healthcare professionals</strong> and workplace responders, including:</p>
<ul>
<li>Emergency response teams</li>
<li>Teachers, coaches, and childcare staff</li>
<li>Adult residential caregivers</li>
<li>Fitness instructors and health club personnel</li>
<li>General public looking to be better prepared for emergencies</li>
</ul>
<h3> <strong>Also Approved for Maritime Personnel:</strong></h3>
<p style="text-align: justify;">For individuals seeking a <strong>Merchant Mariner Credential</strong>, this course meets the <strong>USCG Elementary First Aid and CPR requirement</strong> under 46 CFR 11.201. Successful maritime students will receive:</p>
<div style="text-indent: 0px;">
<p><img src="https://www.enrollware.com/sitefiles/coastalcprtraining/Logo/stripes.png" alt="" width="100" align="right" /></p>
</div>
<ul>
<li>A <strong>2-year HSI Adult First Aid | CPR AED certification card</strong></li>
<li>A <strong>HSINST-203 Recognition of Participation</strong> document accepted by the United States Coast Guard</li>
</ul>
<p style="text-align: justify;">This approval is granted by the USCG National Maritime Center and ensures compliance for those pursuing or renewing USCG licenses.</p>
<h3> <strong>Course Format:</strong></h3>
<ul>
<li><strong>In-Person, Instructor-Led:</strong> Includes hands-on skill sessions and guided practice with certified instructors.</li>
</ul>
<h3> <strong>National Recognitions:</strong></h3>
<ul>
<li><strong>OSHA Compliant:</strong> Meets workplace safety training requirements</li>
<li><strong>USCG Accepted:</strong> Approved under course code HSINST-203</li>
<li><strong>FAA, ACA, NREMT Approved:</strong> Recognized by aviation, EMS, and camp staff organizations</li>
</ul>
<p style="text-align: justify;">Whether you're in the classroom, the workplace, or the wheelhouse of a boat&mdash;this course delivers the hands-on confidence and certification you need to respond when it matters most.</p>

<p style="text-align: justify;">The <strong>HSI Adult First Aid | Adult/Child/Infant CPR AED</strong> course is a comprehensive <strong>blended learning</strong> program combining online instruction with an <strong>in-person, instructor-led skills session</strong>. This format allows for flexible <strong>self-paced online learning</strong>&nbsp;while ensuring hands-on practice with <strong>essential life-saving techniques</strong>.</p>
<h3> <strong>Course Highlights:</strong></h3>
<ul>
<li><strong>Blended Learning:</strong> Complete engaging online modules covering first aid, CPR, and AED use, followed by an in-person skills session.</li>
</ul>
<ul>
<li><strong>Comprehensive Coverage:</strong> Learn to respond effectively to emergencies involving <strong>adults, children, and infants</strong>, including choking, cardiac arrest, and trauma</li>
</ul>
<ul>
<li><strong>Up-to-Date Content:</strong> Follows the latest <strong>ILCOR &amp; AHA 2020 Guidelines</strong>&nbsp;for CPR &amp; Emergency Cardiovascular Care (ECC).</li>
</ul>
<h3> <strong>Who Should Enroll?</strong></h3>
<p style="text-align: justify;">This course is perfect for <strong>non-healthcare professionals</strong>&nbsp;who require or desire CPR and first aid training, including:</p>
<ul>
<li>Emergency response teams in workplaces</li>
<li>Fitness trainers and health club staff</li>
<li>Adult residential caregivers</li>
<li>Teachers, coaches, and childcare providers</li>
<li>Anyone interested in gaining essential first aid &amp; CPR skills</li>
</ul>
<h3> <strong>Course Components:</strong></h3>
<ul>
<li><strong>Online Learning:</strong> Complete interactive training modules at your own pace.</li>
<li><strong>In-Person Skills Session:</strong> Attend an instructor-led session for hands-on practice and evaluation.</li>
</ul>
<h3> <strong>Certification:</strong></h3>
<p style="text-align: justify;">Upon successful completion of the online and in-person components, participants will receive a <strong>2-year HSI First Aid | CPR AED certification</strong>.</p>

Adult and Pediatric First Aid/CPR/AED <img src="https://www.enrollware.com/sitefiles/coastalcprtraining/_ARC.png" style="width:25px;float:left;margin-right:5px;"></a></span></div><div class='enrpanel-body'><p>The Adult and Pediatric First Aid/CPR/AED course incorporates the latest science and teaches students to recognize and care for a variety of first aid emergencies such as burns, cuts, scrapes, sudden illnesses, head, neck, back injuries, heat and cold emergencies and how to respond to breathing and cardiac emergencies to help victims of any age - adults (about 12 years and older) and pediatric (infants and children up to 12 years of age).&nbsp;Students who successfully complete this course will receive a certificate for Adult and Pediatric First Aid/CPR/AED valid for two years.</p>

<div><strong> Same-day certification includes both AHA eCard and AMERHA-216 form</strong></div>
<p>The <strong>American Heart Association&rsquo;s Heartsaver&reg; First Aid CPR AED (TOTAL) course</strong> is officially recognized by the <strong>U.S. Coast Guard (USCG)</strong> as meeting the full training requirement for <strong>Elementary First Aid</strong>.</p>
<p>This instructor-led course includes hands-on training in <strong>adult first aid, CPR, AED use, and choking relief</strong>, and is ideal for mariners, maritime professionals, and others seeking credentials that meet USCG standards.</p>
<p><strong>This program meets:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>STCW Code Table A-VI/1-3: Elementary First Aid</li>
<li>46 CFR 11.302(a)(3) and 12.602(a)(3)</li>
<li>46 CFR 11.201(i)(1) &ndash; First Aid &amp; CPR training requirements</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Course ID:</strong> AMERHA-216</p>
<p><strong>Certification:</strong> AHA Heartsaver&reg; eCard (valid for 2 years) and signed USCG form AMERHA-216 provided same day</p>
<p><strong>Duration:</strong> ~2.5 to 3.5 hours depending on group size and skill level</p>
<p style="font-size: 85%; color: gray;"><em>This training is delivered in accordance with the AHA PAM and has been reviewed and accepted by the U.S. Coast Guard National Maritime Center (NMC).</em></p>

<div style="text-align: justify;">The course is ideal for parents, grandparents, caregivers, school groups and students, and others interested in learning how to save a life. Skills are taught using American Heart Association's research-proven practice-while-watching technique, which allows participants to practice on a CPR training manikin while skills are demonstrated in the course video.</div>

<h2 class="h3">Course Content</h2>
<ul>
<li>Adult Hands-Only CPR and AED</li>
<li>Adult CPR With Breaths</li>
<li>Mild and Severe Airway Block: How to Help a Choking Adult&nbsp;</li>
<li>Child CPR and AED&nbsp;</li>
<li>Mild and Severe Airway Block: How to Help a Choking Child&nbsp;</li>
<li>Infant CPR</li>
<li>Mild and Severe Airway Block: How to Help a Choking Infant</li>
</ul>
<div>&nbsp;</div>

<h2> Become a Heartsaver&reg; Instructor</h2>
<p>So, you&rsquo;re ready to teach CPR and First Aid? Let&rsquo;s make it official.</p>
<p>As an <strong>AHA Heartsaver&reg; Instructor</strong>, you&rsquo;ll be able to offer training in:</p>
<ul>
<li>CPR &amp; AED use</li>
<li>First Aid</li>
<li>Pediatric First Aid CPR/AED</li>
<li>K&ndash;12 School Programs</li>
<li>Bloodborne Pathogens</li>
<li>...and more.</li>
</ul>
<p>You&rsquo;ll have the freedom to:</p>
<ul>
<li>Teach at your own workplace or anywhere else you&rsquo;re approved</li>
<li>List your classes on the official AHA class locator</li>
<li>Certify students across the U.S.</li>
</ul>
<h3> What's Included</h3>
<p>Your registration includes:</p>
<ul>
<li><strong>Heartsaver Instructor Essentials</strong> (online course)</li>
<li><strong>Heartsaver Instructor Manual</strong> (digital or print, shipped to you)</li>
<li><strong>In-person Instructor Course</strong> with a live facilitator</li>
<li><strong>Initial Instructor Monitoring</strong> within 6 months</li>
<li><strong>Alignment with our AHA training site</strong> (optional but available)</li>
</ul>
<h3> What You Might Still Need</h3>
<ul>
<li><strong>Current AHA Heartsaver Provider Certification</strong> &ndash; required before your instructor status can be finalized. If you don&rsquo;t have one yet, you can add the provider course during registration.</li>
<li><strong>Heartsaver Student Workbook</strong> &ndash; needed only if completing your provider course as part of this process.</li>
</ul>
<h3> What to Expect</h3>
<ol>
<li>Complete the Instructor Essentials online course (link emailed after registration)</li>
<li>Attend your Instructor Course Day</li>
<li>Complete your monitored session within 6 months of your course</li>
</ol>

<h2> Become a BLS Instructor</h2>
<p>Want to teach CPR professionally &mdash; without the stress of sounding like a robot? You're in the right place.</p>
<p>This course is for anyone looking to certify others in <strong>BLS and Heartsaver-level CPR/First Aid</strong>, whether you're teaching staff at your job, launching your own gig, or just want to expand your skills.</p>
<h3> What&rsquo;s Included</h3>
<p>Your registration includes:</p>
<ul>
<li><strong>BLS Instructor Essentials</strong> (online course)</li>
<li><strong>BLS Instructor Manual</strong> (eBook or print, shipped to you)</li>
<li><strong>BLS Provider Manual</strong> (for reference and student prep)</li>
<li><strong>In-person Instructor Course</strong></li>
<li><strong>Initial Instructor Monitoring</strong> (within 6 months)</li>
<li><strong>Training site alignment</strong> (with us, if needed)</li>
</ul>
<h3> What You Might Still Need</h3>
<ul>
<li><strong>Current AHA BLS Provider Card</strong> &mdash; required before you're officially certified as an instructor. If you don't have one, you can add a BLS course to your registration and complete it before class day.</li>
<li><strong>Demo student for your monitoring day</strong> &mdash; Bring a guest to act as your student and they&rsquo;ll receive a free BLS card. Can&rsquo;t bring someone? Let us know &mdash; we&rsquo;ll help!</li>
</ul>
<h3> What the Process Looks Like</h3>
<ol>

<li>Complete the Instructor Essentials online module</li>

<li>Get monitored while teaching your first class</li>
<li>You're cleared to teach anywhere in the U.S. &mdash; on your terms</li>

<h2> Become an ACLS Instructor</h2>
<p>Ready to teach Advanced Cardiac Life Support (ACLS) and train the next wave of lifesavers? This course is built for experienced providers who want to lead ACLS certification classes &mdash; whether you&rsquo;re training staff, launching your own CPR business, or working as an independent instructor.</p>
<h3> What&rsquo;s Included</h3>
<p>Your registration includes:</p>
<ul>
<li><strong>ACLS Instructor Essentials</strong> (online)</li>
<li><strong>ACLS Instructor Manual</strong> (digital or print, shipped to you)</li>
<li><strong>In-person Instructor Course</strong></li>
<li><strong>Initial Instructor Monitoring</strong> (within 6 months)</li>
<li><strong>Alignment with our training site</strong> if you don&rsquo;t have one</li>
</ul>
<h3> What You Might Still Need</h3>
<ul>
<li><strong>Current AHA ACLS Provider Card</strong> &ndash; required before you're fully certified. If you don't have one, you can add the course to your registration.</li>
<li><strong>ACLS Provider Manual</strong> &ndash; required for review and testing. Not included in this course package, but available if needed.</li>
</ul>

<ol>
<li>Register and complete the Instructor Candidate form (we&rsquo;ll send it to you)</li>
<li>Finish the Instructor Essentials online course</li>
<li>Attend your in-person Instructor Course (includes ACLS skills testing)</li>
<li>Pass: BLS skills test, ACLS megacode, and ACLS provider exam</li>
<li>Get monitored while teaching your first class (at our site or yours)</li>
<li>Pass the Instructor Exam (84% or better)</li>
</ol>

<h2>&nbsp;Become a PALS Instructor</h2>
<p>Teach lifesaving pediatric care with confidence. This course is designed for healthcare providers who want to lead <strong>Pediatric Advanced Life Support (PALS)</strong> classes. <div style="text-align: center; background-color: #222; color: white; padding: 12px; font-weight: bold; border-radius: 4px;">AHA Instructor Trio: BLS, ACLS &amp; PALS</div>
<p><img style="width: 75px; float: right; margin-left: 10px;" src="https://www.enrollware.com/sitefiles/coastalcprtraining/_AHA.png" alt="AHA Instructor Certification" /></p>
<p style="text-align: justify;">This all-inclusive instructor course is designed for experienced healthcare providers who are ready to become certified instructors in <strong>Basic Life Support (BLS)</strong>, <strong>Advanced Cardiac Life Support (ACLS)</strong>, and <strong>Pediatric Advanced Life Support (PALS)</strong> through the American Heart Association (AHA).</p>
<p style="text-align: justify;">Participants must hold valid provider-level certifications in all three disciplines (BLS, ACLS, and PALS) prior to enrollment. The course includes in-depth instruction on AHA teaching methodology, course delivery standards, equipment management, and skills testing practices.</p>
<h3>Course Covers:</h3>
<ul>
<li> AHA instructor requirements, policies, and course structure</li>
<li> How to conduct and evaluate provider skills sessions</li>
<li> How to issue course completion cards and manage rosters</li>
<li> Specific guidance for teaching BLS, ACLS, and PALS curriculum</li>
</ul>
<h3>Course Includes:</h3>
<ul>
<li> Instructor Candidate Workbooks</li>
<li> Access to all instructor materials and course monitoring</li>
<li> AHA Instructor certifications in BLS, ACLS, and PALS (valid 2 years)</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Note:</strong> This course is intensive and best suited for providers with clinical experience and a strong understanding of AHA algorithms.</p>
<p><strong>Pre-course Requirements:</strong> Must hold valid AHA BLS, ACLS, and PALS provider certifications and complete the corresponding AHA Instructor Essentials online modules before the course date. Links will be sent upon registration.</p>

<div style="text-align: center; background-color: #a6192e; color: white; padding: 10px; font-weight: bold;">OSHA 10 &amp; 30 | Construction &amp; General Industry | English &amp; Spanish</div>
<!-- Course Image & Quick Info -->
<p><img style="float: right; padding: 7px; margin: 0 0 10px 10px;" src="https://www.enrollware.com/sitefiles/coastalcprtraining/Class_Images/OTNB.png" alt="OSHA 10 &amp; 30 Training" width="250" /></p>
<!-- Course Overview -->
<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>OSHA Outreach Training</strong> helps workers and supervisors understand workplace hazards, safety precautions, and their rights under OSHA regulations. This program is ideal for those working in <strong>construction, general industry, and related fields</strong>.</p>
<p style="text-align: justify;">Choose from <strong>OSHA 10-Hour or 30-Hour courses</strong> based on your role:</p>
<ul>
<li><strong>OSHA 10-Hour:</strong> Designed for entry-level workers who need basic safety training.</li>
<li><strong>OSHA 30-Hour:</strong> Intended for supervisors, managers, and safety officers.</li>
</ul>
<p style="text-align: justify;">These courses are available in <strong>English &amp; Spanish</strong> and are offered in two industry categories:</p>
<ul>
<li><strong>Construction:</strong> Focuses on safety regulations for construction sites.</li>
<li><strong>General Industry:</strong> Covers workplace safety standards for various industries.</li>
</ul>
<!-- Course Topics -->
<p><strong>Course Topics Include:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>OSHA Standards and Worker Rights</li>
<li>Personal Protective Equipment (PPE)</li>
<li>Fall Protection and Ladder Safety</li>
<li>Electrical Safety Awareness</li>
<li>Scaffold Safety and Hazard Communication</li>
<li>Fire Safety and Emergency Preparedness</li>
<li>Confined Space Entry and Machine Guarding</li>
<li>Workplace Ergonomics and Industrial Hygiene</li>
</ul>
<!-- Certification Details -->
<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>Certification:</strong> Participants who successfully complete the course will receive a <strong>Department of Labor OSHA 10 or 30-Hour Course Completion Card</strong>. Please note: OSHA 10/30 courses must be completed within <strong>180 days</strong> from the start date.</p>
<!-- Important Notices -->
<div style="border: 1px solid #ddd; padding: 10px; margin-top: 15px; background: #f9f9f9;">
<p><strong> Important Information:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>OSHA courses are <strong>100% online</strong> &ndash; No in-person skills evaluation required.</li>
<li>Training must be completed within <strong>180 days</strong> from the start date.</li>
<li>OSHA has <strong>jurisdiction restrictions</strong>: Completion cards are only issued for students within the <strong>U.S. and territories</strong>.</li>
<li><strong>New York City:</strong> These courses do <strong>not</strong> meet the NYC OSHA training requirements.</li>
</ul>
</div>

<h3>STOP THE <span style="color: #ff0000;">BLEED</span><sup>&reg;</sup>&nbsp;Interactive Course</h3>
<p><em>Stop The Bleed</em> is a national campaign that aims to make bleeding control training as commonplace as CPR training. Since a person can bleed out and die in as little as three minutes it is literally a matter of life or death that someone take action immediately, someone who is already there. Remember, until help arrives, YOU are the help.</p>
<p>This interactive course is a virtual alternative to the in-person lecture presentation. The <em>STOP THE BLEED<sup>&reg;</sup></em>&nbsp;Interactive Course guides individuals through the three methods of bleeding control using video demonstrations, interactive learning, and spontaneous quizzes.</p>
<p><em><strong>910CPR</strong> </em>believes strongly that this information is valuable and want to bring this free program to your attention.&nbsp;<strong> The online&nbsp;<em>STOP THE BLEED<sup>&reg;</sup></em>&nbsp;Interactive Course is free to all</strong> and can be taken multiple times to learn and refresh knowledge of the material.&nbsp;</p>
<p style="text-align: justify;">Although the information above is free, to&nbsp;recieve a&nbsp;<em>STOP THE BLEED<sup>&reg;</sup></em> certification, there is a nominal fee to cover materials and manikin wear.&nbsp; There is no obligation to obtain the certification, but it is&nbsp;encouraged that you to choose the practial training to be confident in your understanding of the material.</p>
